"end": 1112}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:5054"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "PAI-1", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9960306882858276, "span": {"begin": 1114, "end": 1119}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:5327"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "tPA", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9951080679893494, "span": {"begin": 1130, "end": 1133}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:5328"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "uPA", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9947884678840637, "span": {"begin": 1134, "end": 1137}}, {"id": ["mesh:D000347"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "hypofibrinolysis", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.999997615814209, "span": {"begin": 1153, "end": 1169}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:710"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "SERPING1", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9919750094413757, "span": {"begin": 1228, "end": 1236}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:2160"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "FXII", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9864635467529297, "span": {"begin": 1246, "end": 1250}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:710"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "SERPING1", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9893789887428284, "span": {"begin": 1280, "end": 1288}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:2160"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "FXII", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9848314523696899, "span": {"begin": 1310, "end": 1314}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:5624"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Protein C", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9960951209068298, "span": {"begin": 1389, "end": 1398}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:5627"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "protein S", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.996382474899292, "span": {"begin": 1400, "end": 1409}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:7056"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "thrombomodulin", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9927999973297119, "span": {"begin": 1414, "end": 1428}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:10068"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "FVa", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9918686151504517, "span": {"begin": 1437, "end": 1440}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:2157"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "FVIIIa", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9951702952384949, "span": {"begin": 1445, "end": 1451}}, {"id": ["CHEBI:17824"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "IPA", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.7176451086997986, "span": {"begin": 1459, "end": 1462}}], "text": "Coagulation is a process that responds to injury by the rapid formation of a clot. Activation of coagulation factor proteins are involved in coagulation. &nbsp;In the extrinsic pathway, platelets, upon the contact with collagen in the injured blood vessel wall, release thromboxane A2 (TXA2) and adenosine 2 phosphates (ADP), leading to the clot formation. Extravascular tissue factor (TF) binds to plasma factor VIIa (FVIIa) and promotes the activation of FXa. Activated FXa assembles with cofactors FVa and FVIIIa on the surface of aggregated platelets, which lead to generation of thrombin (FIIa). Thrombin catalyzes the production of fibrin (FG) which creates a clot. The binding of prekallikrein and high-molecular weight kininogen activate FXIIa in the intrinsic pathway. Many regulators are involved in coagulation system. Plasmin is one of the modulators required for dissolution of the fibrin clot. Plasmin is activated by tissue plasminogen activator (tPA) and urokinase plasminogen activation (uPA). SERPINs inhibit thrombin, plasmin and tPA. For example, SERPINE1 or plasminogen activator inhibitor-1 (PAI-1) inhibits tPA/uPA and results in hypofibrinolysis [Bernard I,et al. Viruses. 2021; 13(1):29.]. In addition, SERPING1 inhibits FXII, and thus down-regulation of SERPING1 lifts suppression of FXII of the intrinsic coagulation cascade [Garvin et al. eLife 2020;9:e59177]. Protein C, protein S and thrombomodulin degrade FVa and FVIIIa. [Ref. IPA, Coagulation System, version60467501, release date: 2020-11-19]", "timestamp": "Fri May 15 21:51:46 +0000 2026"}